    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-10T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-10T03:00:00-05:00" n="520"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13393: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-10T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 10, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 10—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. Embassy’s 115, March 6, 4 p.m.<note n="62" xml:id="d520fn62">Not
                        printed.</note> The Military Attaché of the Embassy has returned from a
                    short trip to Taiyuanfu and Fenchow. It is his opinion that Fenchow will not be
                    occupied by the Communists, although there are Communist troops inoccupation of
                    villages in the vicinity of Fenchow. According to the report of the military
                    commander at Fenchow, some 27, 000 Communist forces have crossed from Shensi
                    into Shansi, but this is believed to be exaggerated. He does not believe that
                    the Communist activity in Shansi has any direct <pb facs="0603" n="508"
                        xml:id="pg_508"/> relation to Sino-Japanese affairs. He reports that six
                    Americans (4 women and 2 men) are now at Fenchow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
